		{
			dependencies: ["5C5C000000000008"]
			description: ["Light machine guns — the M249, RPK, and ultimately the minigun — are sustained-fire platforms built on &eIV&r motors, with the largest weapons reaching into &eLuV&r components. An LMG's job is uptime: a belt or drum that keeps firing through an entire add wave without a reload window. The ammunition bill is enormous, which is the real gate — do not build an LMG until your ammo production line can feed it without bankrupting your brass supply."]
